HEADWORD: Unifacial
<hw>U`ni*fa"cial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets>
+ <ets>facial</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having but one front surface; <as>as,
some foliaceous corals are <ex>unifacial</ex>, the polyp mouths being
confined to one surface</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

